FT  18 AUG 93 / Radio agency lists pirate raids
THE Radiocommunications Agency, part of the Department of Trade and
Industry, carried out 536 raids against pirate radio stations in the past 12
months. This resulted in 200 convictions.
In its annual report, published yesterday, the agency said it had achieved
an overall 2 per cent efficiency gain in a wide range of customer-service
areas during the year.
